{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1778291102,"nonce":"09T4IUXgC0JBWAsa3KIBIIFZczI=","title":"CLAUDE.md addition: post-training-run protocol (commit run-config + log results)","message":"After every training run on RunPod (or any remote compute), the agent should follow a consistent protocol to ensure results are tracked, artifacts are committed, and coordination surfaces are updated.\n\n## Proposed Protocol\n\nAfter a training run completes:\n\n1. **Commit run-specs**: Move `run.json` spec files from `_artifacts/\u003cexp\u003e/runs/\u003clabel\u003e/` to `results/\u003cexp\u003e/runs/\u003clabel\u003e/run.json` and commit on a feature branch via `agent-commit --issue \u003ctracking-issue-id\u003e`.\n2. **Submit auth request**: Submit a `mandible auth request` to merge the feature branch into `main`.\n3. **Comment on tracking issue**: Add a comment on the relevant feature/umbrella issue (e.g. the experiment umbrella) with the key results (metric table, winning condition, key findings).\n4. **Cross-ref training-methods coord** (`c99ad9d`): If the run reflects a training-method decision (new method, new loss term, new adversary class), add a comment on `c99ad9d` cross-referencing the tracking issue and noting the finding.\n5. **Cross-ref analyses coord** (`4d38c15`): If the run motivates new analyses or tier shifts, add a comment on `4d38c15` cross-referencing the relevant issues.\n\n## Motivation\n\nThis protocol is currently implicit. The 2026-05-08 baseline matrix session demonstrated the gap: the variance analysis was completed and issue comments were filed, but the `run.json` spec files were not committed until a separate follow-up task. Codifying it closes this workflow gap.\n\n## Target Location\n\nProject-level `CLAUDE.md` in the rlrmp repo (not global CLAUDE.md — the RunPod runbook is already project-scoped there). Add under a new **## Post-Training-Run Protocol** section, after the RunPod Deploy Runbook.\n\n## Proposed Wording (for review)\n\n```\n## Post-Training-Run Protocol\n\nAfter every remote training run (RunPod, Modal, etc.) completes:\n\n1. **Commit run-specs on a feature branch**: Move `run.json` spec files from `_artifacts/\u003cexp\u003e/\u003clabel\u003e/` to `results/\u003cexp\u003e/runs/\u003cgroup\u003e__\u003cvariant\u003e/run.json` and commit via `agent-commit --issue \u003ctracking-issue\u003e`.\n2. **Submit auth request**: `mandible auth request feature/\u003cname\u003e --issue \u003ctracking-issue\u003e --no-watch`.\n3. **Comment on tracking issue**: Key metrics table + winning condition + key findings.\n4. **Comment on `c99ad9d`** (training-methods coord) if the run reflects a training-method decision.\n5. **Comment on `4d38c15`** (analyses coord) if new analyses or tier shifts are motivated.\n\nDo all five steps before closing out the session that produced the run.\n```\n\n## Context\n\nThis issue was prompted by the 2026-05-08 session baseline matrix run where step 1 was deferred until a separate task. Per the Memory Files vs Workflow Instructions convention, this must be a CLAUDE.md issue rather than a memory entry.","files":null}]}